Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @boiled water{500%ml} for the risotto into a
#measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock paste{20%g} and stir well to combine -
this is your chicken stock.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel
first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks. Pop it onto a large #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden,
~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small
pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{60%g} and fry until it starts to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the onion and fry until starting to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}, then add the
garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g} to the pan, then stir and cook until the edges
are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in your chicken stock and bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{}
on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water
has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @hazelnuts{25%g}(roughly chopped). Pick the
@rosemary{1}(leaves picked, stalks discarded and roughly chopped).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the hazelnuts, rosemary, @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}
and @olive oil{for the crumb}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, toast the
crumb mixture until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch it like a hawk as it can burn easily. Set aside for later.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the
@butter{20%g}, @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and roasted butternut
squash.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the butternut and chorizo risotto between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the rosemary and hazelnut crumb to finish.

Enjoy!